where p
1 is the fraction of mutations located at a type of interface (n
mut, region/n
mut, total), and p
2 is the fraction of amino acid residues that belong to that type of interface (n
res, region/n
res, total). Z scores for odds ratios were calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
